    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-01-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="137"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                <head>137. Memorandum From Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1"
                        >Vance</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1"
                        >Carter</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d137fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                        Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, Subject File, Box 19, Evening Reports
                        (State), 1/78. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1978-01-31">January 31, 1978</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Omitted here is information unrelated to Panama.]</p>
                <p>6. <hi rend="italic">Panama:</hi>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BRC_2">Bob Byrd</persName> asked <persName
                        corresp="#p_WC_1">Warren</persName> to come up to talk about the floor
                    debate on the Treaties, and they were joined by <persName corresp="#p_BHH_1"
                        >Howard Baker</persName>. When the debate begins next week,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d137fn2">The week of February 6.</note> both <persName
                        corresp="#p_BHF_1">Byrd</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BHH_1"
                        >Baker</persName>, and no doubt others, will have opening statements, after
                    which the Neutrality Treaty will be discussed article by article. Amendments
                    will be in order at the time, and <persName corresp="#p_BHF_1">Byrd</persName>
                    will try to insure that the Amendments regarding <pb facs="0403" n="368"
                        xml:id="pg_368"/> the October 14 Statement will be introduced, with many
                    sponsors, prior to the recess.<note n="3" xml:id="d137fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> wrote in the left margin:
                        “Ok—I’ll show <persName corresp="#p_BHF_1">Byrd</persName> the TV speech—He
                        asked.” See <ref target="#d99fn6">footnote 6, Document 99.</ref>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_BHF_1">Byrd</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BHH_1"
                        >Baker</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_WC_1">Warren</persName> will
                    meet again tomorrow morning<note n="4" xml:id="d137fn4">February 1.</note> along
                    with White House and State Congressional relations people to assess the vote
                    count, Senator by Senator, and discuss how we can improve our situation. They
                    will also discuss our plans for supporting our side in the debate.</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is information unrelated to Panama.]</p>
            </div>
